# SuperAdminCopilot — Hardening Assessment

> Full architectural review of the pipeline, trace persistence, background services, and operational guards.
> Updated: 2026-05-13

---

## 1. Architecture Summary

```mermaid
graph TD
    Q["User Question"] --> PF["Preflight (regex refusal)"]
    PF --> OG["OperationalGuard (kill switch + rate limit)"]
    OG --> RT["Router (HybridIntentRouter + probes)"]
    RT -->|Conversational| CH["ConversationalHandler"]
    RT -->|Knowledge| KH["KnowledgeMatchHandler"]
    RT -->|Metadata| MH["MetadataHandler"]
    RT -->|SemanticSearch| SS["SemanticSearchHandler"]
    RT -->|Tool| TH["ToolHandler"]
    RT -->|DataQuery| SE["Shape Engine (27 shapes)"]
    SE -->|miss| LP["LLM Planner"]
    SE -->|hit| CO["Compiler"]
    LP --> CO
    CO --> VA["Validator (AST + Intent + Shape)"]
    VA --> EX["Executor (PII → CostGate → Cache → ReadOnly)"]
    EX --> EXP["Explainer"]
    EXP --> TR["TraceSink → CopilotTraceHistories"]
```

**Component count**: ~50 classes across 12 namespaces, 27 registered question shapes, 8 resolver types, 4-layer executor chain, 2 background hosted services.

---

## 2. Findings by Severity

### 🔴 Critical — Fix Before Production

| # | Area | Finding | Impact |
|---|------|---------|--------|
| C1 | **RetryBudget scope** | `RetryBudget` is Scoped but `Reset()` is never called explicitly — it relies on DI scope boundaries. If the orchestrator is ever invoked twice within the same HTTP scope (e.g. decomposition sub-questions), the budget carries forward correctly by design. BUT if a middleware or filter re-enters the pipeline, the stale budget silently caps the second entry. | Silent query refusal |
| C2 | **CopilotTraceHistoryStore swallows all exceptions** | [SaveAsync L100](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Services/AI/Copilot/Trace/CopilotTraceHistoryStore.cs#L100-L104) catches `Exception` and returns `null`. A persistent DB failure (connection pool exhaustion, schema mismatch) will silently lose **every** trace with zero alerting — the only signal is a single `LogError` that drowns in noise. | Complete forensic data loss |
| C3 | **ReadOnlyExecutor has no SQL injection guard** | [ReadOnlyExecutor L29-31](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Execution/ReadOnlyExecutor.cs#L29-L31) executes `compiled.Sql` directly. While the compiler produces parameterized SQL, the `CompiledSql` record is a public type — any future code path that constructs one manually bypasses the AST validator. Defence-in-depth requires a final `SELECT`-only assertion here. | Potential data mutation |
| C4 | **PiiRedactingExecutor lazy field is not thread-safe** | [PiiRedactingExecutor L36-37](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Execution/PiiRedactingExecutor.cs#L36-L37) uses `_allSensitive` with a null-check-then-write pattern. As a Singleton wrapping another Singleton, concurrent first-requests can race and one thread sees a partial HashSet. | Sporadic PII leak on cold start |

### 🟠 High — Significant Quality / Reliability Gaps

| # | Area | Finding | Impact |
|---|------|---------|--------|
| H1 | **CopilotOrchestrator size** | 1642 lines with `RunSingleAsync` containing the entire Tier-1 + Tier-2 + shape-engine dispatch + retry loop. Cognitive load makes bugs invisible. | Maintainability risk |
| H2 | **CostGateExecutor opens a separate DB connection** | [CostGateExecutor L79](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Execution/CostGateExecutor.cs#L79) opens its own `IDbConnectionFactory.Open()` for SHOWPLAN, then ReadOnlyExecutor opens ANOTHER. Under load this doubles connection consumption per query. | Connection pool pressure |
| H3 | **SqlCompiler is 1390+ lines** | Partial-class split started (`SqlCompiler.Aggregation.cs`, `.Helpers.cs`) but the main file still holds BuildSelect/BuildFrom/BuildWhere/BuildGroupBy/BuildOrderBy/QualifyColumnsInExpression. A single typo in the 800-line expression qualifier breaks every query. | High blast radius |
| H4 | **LlmPlanner NJsonSchema validation removed** | [LlmPlanner L121-123](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Pipeline/Stages/LlmPlanner.cs#L121-L123) — schema validation was removed due to PascalCase/camelCase mismatch. The comment says "the deserialize step handles real malformed JSON" but `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<QuerySpec>` with `PropertyNameCaseInsensitive=true` silently ignores unknown properties. A planner that emits `{ "rout": "Tickets" }` (typo) produces an empty spec that compiles to `SELECT * FROM` — a table scan. | Silent wrong answers |
| H5 | **OperationalGuard rate limiter is in-memory only** | [OperationalGuard](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Pipeline/OperationalGuard.cs) uses `ConcurrentDictionary` — lost on app restart, not shared across instances in a scaled-out deployment. | Rate limit bypass in multi-instance |
| H6 | **TraceRetentionHostedService timer drift** | The service loops with `Task.Delay(interval)` but never accounts for the time spent in `ExecuteDeleteAsync`. Over weeks, the actual pruning interval drifts. More importantly, if the delete takes longer than the interval, back-pressure is never signaled. | Unbounded trace growth |
| H7 | **CachingExecutor uses SHA-256 over full SQL text** | [CachingExecutor L72-87](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Execution/CachingExecutor.cs#L72-L87) serializes all parameters to JSON, concatenates, then SHA-256 hashes. For large `IN (...)` filter lists this allocates a multi-KB string per cache lookup. Also, `JsonSerializer.Serialize(kv.Value)` on a `DBNull` or `DateTime` uses default formatting — two semantically identical dates with different `ToString()` forms miss the cache. | Cache misses, GC pressure |

### 🟡 Medium — Technical Debt / Correctness Risks

| # | Area | Finding |
|---|------|---------|
| M1 | **Duplicate `Truncate` methods** | `CopilotOrchestrator.Truncate(string,int)` at L1446 and `LlmPlanner.Truncate(string,int)` at L193 are identical private statics. |
| M2 | **`IOptions<>` vs `IOptionsMonitor<>`** | Most services inject `IOptions<CopilotOptions>` (captured once at construction). But the DI registration uses `ValidateOnStart` + `IPostConfigureOptions`. Runtime hot-reload via the Settings UI only takes effect on next scope creation for Scoped services; Singletons (compiler, shapes, resolvers, all executors) keep stale values forever. |
| M3 | **`ExtractKeyIds` column-name heuristic** | [CopilotOrchestrator L1398-1401](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Pipeline/CopilotOrchestrator.cs#L1398-L1401) picks the first column ending in "Id" — if the result has `StatusId` before `TicketId`, it threads status IDs into the next sub-question instead of ticket IDs. |
| M4 | **`NaturalKeyResolver` compiles regex per call** | [Resolvers.cs L374](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Semantic/Resolvers.cs#L374) — `Regex.IsMatch(id, e.NaturalKeyFormat!)` creates a new Regex object for every entity × every question. With 10 entities, that's 10 regex compilations per request. |
| M5 | **`ColumnResolver.ToPascal` crashes on single-char input** | [Resolvers.cs L174](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Semantic/Resolvers.cs#L174) — `w[1..]` on a 1-char word produces empty string, which is fine, but a 0-char word (from consecutive spaces) would throw `IndexOutOfRangeException`. The `RemoveEmptyEntries` flag protects against this today, but the code is fragile. |
| M6 | **`BuildUnknownTableReply` uses `List.Contains` with comparer** | [CopilotOrchestrator L1495](file:///c:/Work/Lern/Improve/v1/ServiceOpsAI/Areas/SuperAdminCopilot/Pipeline/CopilotOrchestrator.cs#L1495) — `suggestions.Contains(e.Name, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase)` is O(n) per check; should be a HashSet for correctness at scale. |
| M7 | **Shape engine registration order is fragile** | 27 shapes registered as `IQuestionShape` — tie-breaking is DI registration order. No runtime assertion or test verifies that registration order hasn't drifted. A new shape inserted at the wrong position can shadow an existing one. |

